---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Zambia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/zambia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Zimbabwe for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/zimbabwe' },
  { title: 'Botswana for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/botswana' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'zambiaFit', header: 'Zambia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ZMW$12,500-17,850/mo', zambiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ZMW$14,625-20,900/mo', zambiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ZMW$11,250-16,065/mo', zambiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ZMW$10,450-14,930/mo', zambiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Madison, ZSIC)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'ZMW$2,000-5,000/mo', zambiaFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'ZMW$11,250-17,850', annual: 'ZMW$135K-214.2K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'ZMW$15,430-23,800', annual: 'ZMW$185.2K-285.6K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'ZMW$20,750-31,975', annual: 'ZMW$249K-383.7K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'ZMW$500-1,500/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'ZMW$3,000-8,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Zambia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Zambia. Victoria Falls, safari, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Zambia"
  subheadline="Zambia offers Victoria Falls, abundant wildlife, English as official language, and peaceful democracy—an authentic African safari destination with warm hospitality."
  heroImage="/images/countries/zambia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Zambia</h2>
  <p>
    Zambia offers Victoria Falls (shared with Zimbabwe), South Luangwa safari, English as official language, and one of Africa's most peaceful democracies. For adventurous retirees seeking authentic African experience with political stability, Zambia delivers exceptional wildlife and natural beauty.
  </p>

  <p>
    Lusaka is the capital with best healthcare. Livingstone provides Victoria Falls access. South Luangwa and Lower Zambezi offer premier safari. Most expats choose Lusaka for healthcare; Livingstone for tourism lifestyle; safari areas for ultimate adventure.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; South Africa backup common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (official); local languages</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ZMW$20,000-40,000/month (~$800-1,600 USD); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; pleasant dry season</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Peaceful; wildlife-rich; hospitable</li>
      <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> Johannesburg 2-hour flight</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Zambia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Zambia healthcare is limited—Lusaka private hospitals (Coptic, Care for Business) provide reasonable care. Public system underfunded. Complex cases typically evacuate to South Africa (Johannesburg 2-hour flight). Safari areas have minimal healthcare. International insurance with evacuation essential.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare improving but still limited outside Lusaka. Many doctors trained internationally. Private care affordable for routine needs. South Africa provides essential backup for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">South Africa Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      South Africa provides essential medical backup—Johannesburg is 2-hour flight with world-class hospitals. Safari areas require evacuation to Lusaka then South Africa. Include South Africa in insurance coverage. Don't rely solely on local healthcare.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Zambia has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-90 days available on arrival or e-visa. Single/multiple entry options.
  </p>

  <h3>KAZA UniVisa</h3>
  <p>
    Multi-country visa for Zambia and Zimbabwe. Good for Victoria Falls both sides.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Employment Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For employment. Some semi-retired professionals use with tourism businesses.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories. Apply through immigration.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Zambia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> South Africa coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Zambia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with South Africa evacuation coverage essential. Lusaka private care handles routine needs. Safari areas need robust evacuation. Johannesburg provides world-class backup. Don't economize on coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Zambia, South Africa evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Zambia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Southern Africa network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> World-class healthcare nearby</li>
    <li><strong>Safari coverage:</strong> Remote area evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with South Africa evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Zambia (ZMW ~25 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Lusaka base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Southern Africa focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Victoria Falls Tourism, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month income. Residence permit. Livingstone.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with South Africa evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ZMW$13,500/month (~$540). Falls lifestyle; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Safari Lodge Owner, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,000/month income. Business permit. South Luangwa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global premium with maximum evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ZMW$17,000/month (~$680). Remote location; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: NGO Worker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Residence permit. Lusaka.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Southern Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ZMW$11,250/month (~$450). City life; regional access.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Zambia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of Africa's most peaceful countries. Low violent crime. Peaceful transitions of power since independence. Safe for tourists and expats. Normal precautions in cities. Wildlife areas very secure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English sufficient?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—English is official language. Business, government, healthcare all in English. Over 70 local languages but English is unifying. No language barrier for English speakers. British colonial heritage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Zambia or Zimbabwe side of Victoria Falls?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Both excellent—Zambia gets closer to falls, "Devil's Pool" experience. Zimbabwe arguably better panoramic views. KAZA visa allows both sides. Many choose Zambia for stability and easier logistics. Livingstone more developed than Vic Falls town.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the safari like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—South Luangwa is one of Africa's premier parks. Lower Zambezi offers riverside safari. Walking safaris pioneered here. Less crowded than East Africa. Authentic, intimate wildlife experiences. World-class for leopard sightings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Zambia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Zambia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
